answers.body_markdown:
You should provide a service that&#39;s supposed to be a singleton service only once at root level. You&#39;re currently providing `CartService` in two different modules which leads to two different instances of `CartService` being created. 

If you&#39;re using Angular 6+ remove `CartService` from all providers lists and add `providedIn: &#39;root&#39;`

```js
@Injectable({
  providedIn: &#39;root&#39;,
})
export class CartService {
}
```

If you&#39;re using Angular 5 and below only add `CartService` to the providers list of your root module.

